Binius Commitment Scheme — License & Provenance
===============================================

SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT

Copyright (c) 2025-2026 The Soqucoin Core developers

Original work by Soqucoin: a clean-room implementation of a Binius-style binary-
field commitment scheme, used as the foundation for the Sangria recursion layer
(see `src/crypto/sangria/`). Licensed under the MIT License; the full license
text is in the repository root `COPYING`.

This module implements a published cryptographic construction (binary-field /
"Binius" commitments); it is not derived from third-party source code.
References to "irreducible polynomial", "tower field", etc. in the source are
standard mathematical terminology, not third-party attributions.
